WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.780
The word "biodynamic" may be quickly misinterpreted.

2
00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:09.960
The way I would like you to interpret it in relation to my course,

3
00:00:10.060 --> 00:00:14.260
is that I explain ontogenetic developmental movement.

4
00:00:15.220 --> 00:00:18.840
This is what I call biodynamics, the dynamics of life.

5
00:00:19.440 --> 00:00:22.540
And how, somehow, it is organized by a creative genius,

6
00:00:22.720 --> 00:00:27.360
which can give rise to a kind of emergence of originality, like that, which appears.

7
00:00:28.047 --> 00:00:31.067
It's quite wonderful, ultimately.

8
00:00:31.267 --> 00:00:36.147
Now, you know, I think, a complement to the craniosacral system,

9
00:00:36.207 --> 00:00:38.067
which was perhaps simply anatomical at first,

10
00:00:38.547 --> 00:00:41.727
which now perhaps becomes embryological and dynamic.